column11:
  In this paper we give necessary and sufficient conditions on the
compatibility of a $k$th order homogeneous linear elliptic differential
operator $\mathbb{A}$ and differential constraint $\mathcal{C}$ for solutions
of \begin{align*}
  \mathbb{A} u=f\quad\text{subject to}\quad \mathcal{C} f=0\quad\text{ in
}\mathbb{R}^n \end{align*} to satisfy the estimates \begin{align*}
\|D^{k-j}u\|_{L^{\frac{n}{n-j}}(\mathbb{R}^n)}\leq c\|f\|_{L^1(\mathbb{R}^n)}
\end{align*} for $j\in \{1,\ldots,\min\{k,n-1\}\}$ and \begin{align*}
\|D^{k-n}u\|_{L^{\infty}(\mathbb{R}^n)}\leq c\|f\|_{L^1(\mathbb{R}^n)}
\end{align*} when $k\geq n$.

